How to Profit
data.description: As the Finals MVP of APEX Season 4, Overwatch League Grand Finals MVP in 2018 and all-around star DPS, if there’s one thing Junyoung Park knows, it’s ‘Profit’. Danny Lim sits down with the London Spitfire big shot to review his pro-gaming journey.

data.title: OGE’s Redemption
data.description: Minseok “OGE” Son, the Dallas Fuel’s star tank sits down to discuss the struggles of replacing xQc in 2018, his 4-game suspension, and how the raw emotions of the Dallas Homestand affected him.

data.title: Sinatraa: Top of the Charts
data.description: San Francisco Shock’s Sinatraa walks us through his hyped debut, how he has dealt with negativity, and his maturation in to one of the league’s top players.

data.title: My Hero: Zenyatta
data.description: Hear from Hangzhou Spark's BeBe, Los Angeles Gladiators' Shaz, San Francisco Shock's Viol2t, and New York Excelsior's JJoNak speak on how you can maximize Zenyatta's potential! data.title: Hangzhou Spark’s guxue and Krystal: Access Granted
data.description: Overwatch League insider Emily Tang picks up guxue and Krystal of the Hangzhou Spark to go check out a cat cafe. Hear all about the music that get these pros in the zone before taking the stage, as well as what players they admire in the league. This is Access Granted presented by Toyota.

data.title: On Point with babybay
data.description: The Atlanta Reign’s newest star, Andrej “babybay” Francisty, sits down with Malik Forte to discuss his long and winding road to the Overwatch League, battling through adversity, and how a premonition helped lead to the biggest upset in league history.

data.title: Titans Toppled
data.description: Having not had the taste of a loss since July of 2018, Team Runaway turned Vancouver Titans finally fell to the San Francisco Shock in the Stage 2 finals. The Titans have a strong message for the rest of the league for their remaining matches.

data.title: Ryujehong: An Overwatch Dynasty
data.description: Cited as the “O.G.” of Overwatch and as the inspiration for so many pros to pick up the game, Jehong “ryujehong” Ryu reviews his storied career and his legacy as a pro-gamer.
